        -1664,
        608
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.from }} asks: {{ $json.text }}\n\nAnswer using kubectl_read and/or promql. Be concise \u2014 this is a Telegram chat reply.\nFormat your response clearly with emojis. Keep it under 300 words.",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a Kubernetes SRE assistant answering questions via Telegram.\n\nYou have two tools:\n1. kubectl_read \u2014 any read-only kubectl command. Parameter: \"command\"\n2. promql \u2014 any PromQL query. Parameter: \"query\" (single quotes for label selectors)\n\nRules:\n- Be concise \u2014 this is a chat interface, not a report\n- Use emojis to make status clear (\u2705 \u274c \u26a0\ufe0f \ud83d\udcca)\n- Always run at least one tool before answering\n- If asked about a specific namespace/pod, focus your commands there\n\nIf you diagnose an issue that requires a write action (restart, scale, rollback, delete, apply, cordon, drain), end your response with exactly:\nWRITE_NEEDED: <kubectl command>\nExample: WRITE_NEEDED: rollout restart deployment/payments-app -n prod\n\nDo NOT say you cannot execute commands. Your job is to diagnose and recommend \u2014 a human approves all write actions."
        }
      },
      "id": "3f942e69-888a-4377-ab32-a5d2c5c23a72",
      "name": "K8s Assistant",
